[Re: ProMED-mail Venezuelan hemorrhagic fever - Venezuela: (PO) 20120313.1069429]
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The recent posting in ProMED described 3 arenaviruses found in South America: Guanarito virus, Machupo virus, and Junin virus.

3 additional human pathogenic arenaviruses have been reported in the Americas: Sabia virus (Brazilian hemorrhagic fever) first reported in Sao Paulo in 1990; Whitewater Arroyo virus implicated in cases of fatal hemorrhagic fever in California during 1999 to 2000; and Ocozocoautla de Espinosa virus, recently described as a possible cause of hemorrhagic fever in southern Mexico.

References
----------
1. Berger SA: American Hemorrhagic Fevers: Global Status, 2012. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/american-hemorrhagic-fevers-global-status/
2. Cajimat MNB, Milazzo ML, Bradley RD, Fulhorst CF: Ocozocoautla de Espinosa virus and hemorrhagic fever, Mexico. Emerg Infect Dis 2012; 18(3): 401-5 [http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/18/3/11-1602_article.htm]

